node.title: First NSW Omicron case in hospital among 10 new infections of the variant
node.alt: A woman wearing protective gear stands next to a car
node.description: NSW Health reports a person is hospitalised after contracting the Omicron variant — the first since the new strain landed in Australia.
node.content:
["A person infected with the Omicron variant of COVID-19 has been admitted to hospital, health authorities say.", "It is the first time an Omicron case has been hospitalised in Australia since the variant landed in late November.", "There were another 10 confirmed cases of the new strain\u00a0identified in the 24 hours to 8pm last night, taking the total number of Omicron cases in NSW to 55.", "NSW Health said more cases were expected to be confirmed pending the results of genomic testing.", "Authorities believe nightclub goers at\u00a0Newcastle's Argyle House may have been exposed to the variant on Wednesday night and Thursday morning.", "Confirmed COVID-19 cases, linked to an outbreak on a Sydney party boat on December 3, visited the Argyle House between 9pm on December 8 and 3am on December 9.", "NSW Health says it is likely they were infected with Omicron.", "", "
Newcastle's The Argyle House is a new exposure venue.(Supplied)
", "The 10 new cases were part of 485 new COVID-19 infections recorded in the state.", "NSW Health's John Hall said a public health investigation was underway into the transmission of the virus at the Argyle nightclub.", "\"This is one of a\u00a0number of large social venues \u2014 such as pubs,\u00a0club and party settings \u2014\u00a0where there is increasing COVID-19 transmission,\" he said.", "\"This is contributing to the rising cases in NSW, and we want to reiterate just how important it is for people not to attend social functions if they have any symptoms, even if\u00a0they're mild.\"", "Asked if he was concerned at the news, Federal Health Minister Greg Hunt said\u00a0NSW Health had shown itself to be \"one of the world's leading public health agencies\" with \"world-class infection control\".", "\"So we have high confidence in their ability to contain this\u00a0within that environment,\" he told reporters.\u00a0", "NSW's vaccination rate for people aged 16 and over sat at 93.1 per cent fully vaccinated on Sunday morning.", "In the\u00a012 to 15 age group, 77.7 per cent of eligible children had received two vaccine doses.", "", "
Why we hear about some COVID-19 variants more than others
"]
